---
alwaysApply: true
---

- Strict types. No `any`. Use `unknown` + narrowing for complex types.
- If forced to use type assertion, add a TODO comment explaining why.
- const > let. Never var.
- async/await over .then()
- camelCase vars, PascalCase components/types.
- Keep functions single-responsibility. Split only when doing 2+ things.
- Early returns over nested ifs.
